userAgent: Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10_12_6) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/62.0.3202.89 Safari/537.36

is-on-https.name: is-on-https
is-on-https.helpText: All sites should be protected with HTTPS, even ones that don't handle sensitive data. HTTPS prevents intruders from tampering with or passively listening in on the communications between your app and your users, and is a prerequisite for HTTP/2 and many new web platform APIs. [Learn more](https://developers.google.com/web/tools/lighthouse/audits/https).

first-meaningful-paint.name: first-meaningful-paint
first-meaningful-paint.helpText: First meaningful paint measures when the primary content of a page is visible. [Learn more](https://developers.google.com/web/tools/lighthouse/audits/first-meaningful-paint).

speed-index-metric.name: speed-index-metric
speed-index-metric.helpText: Speed Index shows how quickly the contents of a page are visibly populated. [Learn more](https://developers.google.com/web/tools/lighthouse/audits/speed-index).

screenshot-thumbnails.name: screenshot-thumbnails
screenshot-thumbnails.helpText: This is what the load of your site looked like.

estimated-input-latency.name: estimated-input-latency
estimated-input-latency.helpText: The score above is an estimate of how long your app takes to respond to user input, in milliseconds. There is a 90% probability that a user encounters this amount of latency, or less. 10% of the time a user can expect additional latency. If your score is higher than Lighthouse's target score, users may perceive your app as laggy. [Learn more](https://developers.google.com/web/tools/lighthouse/audits/estimated-input-latency).

first-interactive.name: first-interactive
first-interactive.helpText: The first point at which necessary scripts of the page have loaded and the CPU is idle enough to handle most user input.

consistently-interactive.name: consistently-interactive
consistently-interactive.helpText: The point at which most network resources have finished loading and the CPU is idle for a prolonged period.

user-timings.name: user-timings
user-timings.helpText: Consider instrumenting your app with the User Timing API to create custom, real-world measurements of key user experiences. [Learn more](https://developers.google.com/web/tools/lighthouse/audits/user-timing).

critical-request-chains.name: critical-request-chains
critical-request-chains.helpText: The Critical Request Chains below show you what resources are required for first render of this page. Improve page load by reducing the length of chains, reducing the download size of resources, or deferring the download of unnecessary resources. [Learn more](https://developers.google.com/web/tools/lighthouse/audits/critical-request-chains).

manifest-short-name-length.name: manifest-short-name-length
manifest-short-name-length.description: Manifest's `short_name` will be truncated when displayed on homescreen
manifest-short-name-length.helpText: Make your app's `short_name` fewer than 12 characters to ensure that it's not truncated on homescreens. [Learn more](https://developers.google.com/web/tools/lighthouse/audits/manifest-short_name-is-not-truncated).

deprecations.name: deprecations
deprecations.helpText: Deprecated APIs will eventually be removed from the browser. [Learn more](https://www.chromestatus.com/features#deprecated).

accesskeys.name: accesskeys
accesskeys.helpText: Access keys let users quickly focus a part of the page. For proper navigation, each access key must be unique. [Learn more](https://dequeuniversity.com/rules/axe/2.2/accesskeys).

aria-allowed-attr.name: aria-allowed-attr
aria-allowed-attr.helpText: Each ARIA `role` supports a specific subset of `aria-*` attributes. Mismatching these invalidates the `aria-*` attributes. [Learn more](https://dequeuniversity.com/rules/axe/2.2/aria-allowed-attr).

aria-required-attr.name: aria-required-attr
aria-required-attr.helpText: Some ARIA roles have required attributes that describe the state of the element to screen readers. [Learn more](https://dequeuniversity.com/rules/axe/2.2/aria-required-attr).

aria-required-children.name: aria-required-children
aria-required-children.description: Elements with `[role]` that require specific children `[role]`s, are present.
aria-required-children.helpText: Some ARIA parent roles must contain specific child roles to perform their intended accessibility functions. [Learn more](https://dequeuniversity.com/rules/axe/2.2/aria-required-children).

aria-required-parent.name: aria-required-parent
aria-required-parent.description: `[role]`s are contained by their required parent element.
aria-required-parent.helpText: Some ARIA child roles must be contained by specific parent roles to properly perform their intended accessibility functions. [Learn more](https://dequeuniversity.com/rules/axe/2.2/aria-required-parent).

aria-roles.name: aria-roles
aria-roles.helpText: ARIA roles must have valid values in order to perform their intended accessibility functions. [Learn more](https://dequeuniversity.com/rules/axe/2.2/aria-roles).

aria-valid-attr-value.name: aria-valid-attr-value
aria-valid-attr-value.helpText: Assistive technologies, like screen readers, can't interpret ARIA attributes with invalid values. [Learn more](https://dequeuniversity.com/rules/axe/2.2/aria-valid-attr-value).

aria-valid-attr.name: aria-valid-attr
aria-valid-attr.description: `[aria-*]` attributes are valid and not misspelled.
aria-valid-attr.helpText: Assistive technologies, like screen readers, can't interpret ARIA attributes with invalid names. [Learn more](https://dequeuniversity.com/rules/axe/2.2/aria-valid-attr).

audio-caption.name: audio-caption
audio-caption.helpText: Captions make audio elements usable for deaf or hearing-impaired users, providing critical information such as who is talking, what they're saying, and other non-speech information. [Learn more](https://dequeuniversity.com/rules/axe/2.2/audio-caption).

button-name.name: button-name
button-name.helpText: When a button doesn't have an accessible name, screen readers announce it as "button", making it unusable for users who rely on screen readers. [Learn more](https://dequeuniversity.com/rules/axe/2.2/button-name).

bypass.name: bypass
bypass.description: The page contains a heading, skip link, or landmark region.
bypass.helpText: Adding ways to bypass repetitive content lets keyboard users navigate the page more efficiently. [Learn more](https://dequeuniversity.com/rules/axe/2.2/bypass).

value.description: Ensures the contrast between foreground and background colors meets WCAG 2 AA contrast ratio thresholds
value.help: Elements must have sufficient color contrast

color-contrast.name: color-contrast
color-contrast.description: Background and foreground colors do not have a sufficient contrast ratio.
color-contrast.helpText: Low-contrast text is difficult or impossible for many users to read. [Learn more](https://dequeuniversity.com/rules/axe/2.2/color-contrast).

definition-list.name: definition-list
definition-list.description: `<dl>`'s contain only properly-ordered `<dt>` and `<dd>` groups, `<script>` or `<template>` elements.
definition-list.helpText: When definition lists are not properly marked up, screen readers may produce confusing or inaccurate output. [Learn more](https://dequeuniversity.com/rules/axe/2.2/definition-list).

dlitem.name: dlitem
dlitem.description: Definition list items are wrapped in `<dl>` elements.
dlitem.helpText: Definition list items (`<dt>` and `<dd>`) must be wrapped in a parent `<dl>` element to ensure that screen readers can properly announce them. [Learn more](https://dequeuniversity.com/rules/axe/2.2/dlitem).

document-title.name: document-title
document-title.helpText: Screen reader users use page titles to get an overview of the contents of the page. [Learn more](https://dequeuniversity.com/rules/axe/2.2/document-title).

duplicate-id.name: duplicate-id
duplicate-id.description: `[id]` attributes on the page are unique.
duplicate-id.helpText: The value of an id attribute must be unique to prevent other instances from being overlooked by assistive technologies. [Learn more](https://dequeuniversity.com/rules/axe/2.2/duplicate-id).

frame-title.name: frame-title
frame-title.helpText: Screen reader users rely on frame titles to describe the contents of frames. [Learn more](https://dequeuniversity.com/rules/axe/2.2/frame-title).

value.description: Ensures every HTML document has a lang attribute
value.help: <html> element must have a lang attribute

html-has-lang.name: html-has-lang
html-has-lang.description: `<html>` element does not have a `[lang]` attribute.
html-has-lang.helpText: If a page doesn't specify a lang attribute, a screen reader assumes that the page is in the default language that the user chose when setting up the screen reader. If the page isn't actually in the default language, then the screen reader might not announce the page's text correctly. [Learn more](https://dequeuniversity.com/rules/axe/2.2/html-lang).

html-lang-valid.name: html-lang-valid
html-lang-valid.description: `<html>` element has a valid value for its `[lang]` attribute.
html-lang-valid.helpText: Specifying a valid [BCP 47 language](https://www.w3.org/International/questions/qa-choosing-language-tags#question) helps screen readers announce text properly. [Learn more](https://dequeuniversity.com/rules/axe/2.2/valid-lang).

image-alt.name: image-alt
image-alt.helpText: Informative elements should aim for short, descriptive alternate text. Decorative elements can be ignored with an empty alt attribute.[Learn more](https://dequeuniversity.com/rules/axe/2.2/image-alt).

input-image-alt.name: input-image-alt
input-image-alt.helpText: When an image is being used as an `<input>` button, providing alternative text can help screen reader users understand the purpose of the button. [Learn more](https://dequeuniversity.com/rules/axe/2.2/input-image-alt).

label.name: label
label.helpText: Labels ensure that form controls are announced properly by assistive technologies, like screen readers. [Learn more](https://dequeuniversity.com/rules/axe/2.2/label).

layout-table.name: layout-table
layout-table.description: Presentational `<table>` elements avoid using `<th>`, `<caption>` or the `[summary]` attribute.
layout-table.helpText: A table being used for layout purposes should not include data elements, such as the th or caption elements or the summary attribute, because this can create a confusing experience for screen reader users. [Learn more](https://dequeuniversity.com/rules/axe/2.2/layout-table).

link-name.name: link-name
link-name.helpText: Link text (and alternate text for images, when used as links) that is discernible, unique, and focusable improves the navigation experience for screen reader users. [Learn more](https://dequeuniversity.com/rules/axe/2.2/link-name).

list.name: list
list.description: Lists contain only `<li>` elements and script supporting elements (`<script>` and `<template>`).
list.helpText: Screen readers have a specific way of announcing lists. Ensuring proper list structure aids screen reader output. [Learn more](https://dequeuniversity.com/rules/axe/2.2/list).

listitem.name: listitem
listitem.description: List items (`<li>`) are contained within `<ul>` or `<ol>` parent elements.
listitem.helpText: Screen readers require list items (`<li>`) to be contained within a parent `<ul>` or `<ol>` to be announced properly. [Learn more](https://dequeuniversity.com/rules/axe/2.2/listitem).

meta-refresh.name: meta-refresh
meta-refresh.description: The document does not use `<meta http-equiv="refresh">`.
meta-refresh.helpText: Users do not expect a page to refresh automatically, and doing so will move focus back to the top of the page. This may create a frustrating or confusing experience. [Learn more](https://dequeuniversity.com/rules/axe/2.2/meta-refresh).

meta-viewport.name: meta-viewport
meta-viewport.description: `[user-scalable="no"]` is not used in the `<meta name="viewport">` element and the `[maximum-scale]` attribute is not less than 5.
meta-viewport.helpText: Disabling zooming is problematic for users with low vision who rely on screen magnification to properly see the contents of a web page. [Learn more](https://dequeuniversity.com/rules/axe/2.2/meta-viewport).

object-alt.name: object-alt
object-alt.helpText: Screen readers cannot translate non-text content. Adding alt text to `<object>` elements helps screen readers convey meaning to users. [Learn more](https://dequeuniversity.com/rules/axe/2.2/object-alt).

tabindex.name: tabindex
tabindex.description: No element has a `[tabindex]` value greater than 0.
tabindex.helpText: A value greater than 0 implies an explicit navigation ordering. Although technically valid, this often creates frustrating experiences for users who rely on assistive technologies. [Learn more](https://dequeuniversity.com/rules/axe/2.2/tabindex).

td-headers-attr.name: td-headers-attr
td-headers-attr.description: Cells in a `<table>` element that use the `[headers]` attribute only refer to other cells of that same table.
td-headers-attr.helpText: Screen readers have features to make navigating tables easier. Ensuring `<td>` cells using the `[headers]` attribute only refer to other cells in the same table may improve the experience for screen reader users. [Learn more](https://dequeuniversity.com/rules/axe/2.2/td-headers-attr).

th-has-data-cells.name: th-has-data-cells
th-has-data-cells.description: `<th>` elements and elements with `[role="columnheader"/"rowheader"]` have data cells they describe.
th-has-data-cells.helpText: Screen readers have features to make navigating tables easier. Ensuring table headers always refer to some set of cells may improve the experience for screen reader users. [Learn more](https://dequeuniversity.com/rules/axe/2.2/th-has-data-cells).

valid-lang.name: valid-lang
valid-lang.helpText: Specifying a valid [BCP 47 language](https://www.w3.org/International/questions/qa-choosing-language-tags#question) on elements helps ensure that text is pronounced correctly by a screen reader. [Learn more](https://dequeuniversity.com/rules/axe/2.2/valid-lang).

video-caption.name: video-caption
video-caption.helpText: When a video provides a caption it is easier for deaf and hearing impaired users to access its information. [Learn more](https://dequeuniversity.com/rules/axe/2.2/video-caption).

video-description.name: video-description
video-description.helpText: Audio descriptions provide relevant information for videos that dialogue cannot, such as facial expressions and scenes. [Learn more](https://dequeuniversity.com/rules/axe/2.2/video-description).

total-byte-weight.name: total-byte-weight
total-byte-weight.helpText: Network transfer size [costs users real money](https://whatdoesmysitecost.com/) and is [highly correlated](http://httparchive.org/interesting.php#onLoad) with long load times. Try to find ways to reduce the size of required files.

offscreen-images.name: offscreen-images
offscreen-images.helpText: Consider lazy-loading offscreen images to improve page load speed and time to interactive. [Learn more](https://developers.google.com/web/tools/lighthouse/audits/offscreen-images).

uses-webp-images.name: uses-webp-images
uses-webp-images.helpText: WebP provides better lossy and lossless compression than PNG or JPEG, which means faster downloads and less data consumption. [Learn more](https://developers.google.com/web/tools/lighthouse/audits/webp).

uses-optimized-images.name: uses-optimized-images
uses-optimized-images.helpText: Optimized images load faster and consume less cellular data. [Learn more](https://developers.google.com/web/tools/lighthouse/audits/optimize-images).

uses-request-compression.name: uses-request-compression
uses-request-compression.helpText: Text-based responses should be served with compression (gzip, deflate or brotli) to minimize total network bytes. [Learn more](https://developers.google.com/web/fundamentals/performance/optimizing-content-efficiency/optimize-encoding-and-transfer).

uses-responsive-images.name: uses-responsive-images
uses-responsive-images.helpText: Serve images that are appropriately-sized to save cellular data and improve load time. [Learn more](https://developers.google.com/web/tools/lighthouse/audits/oversized-images).

dom-size.name: dom-size
dom-size.helpText: Browser engineers recommend pages contain fewer than ~1,500 DOM nodes. The sweet spot is a tree depth < 32 elements and fewer than 60 children/parent element. A large DOM can increase memory usage, cause longer [style calculations](https://developers.google.com/web/fundamentals/performance/rendering/reduce-the-scope-and-complexity-of-style-calculations), and produce costly [layout reflows](https://developers.google.com/speed/articles/reflow). [Learn more](https://developers.google.com/web/fundamentals/performance/rendering/).

external-anchors-use-rel-noopener.name: external-anchors-use-rel-noopener
external-anchors-use-rel-noopener.description: Does not open external anchors using `rel="noopener"`
external-anchors-use-rel-noopener.helpText: Open new tabs using `rel="noopener"` to improve performance and prevent security vulnerabilities. [Learn more](https://developers.google.com/web/tools/lighthouse/audits/noopener).

geolocation-on-start.name: geolocation-on-start
geolocation-on-start.description: Avoids requesting the geolocation permission on page load
geolocation-on-start.helpText: Users are mistrustful of or confused by sites that request their location without context. Consider tying the request to user gestures instead. [Learn more](https://developers.google.com/web/tools/lighthouse/audits/geolocation-on-load).

link-blocking-first-paint.displayValue: 1 resource delayed first paint by 955 ms
link-blocking-first-paint.name: link-blocking-first-paint
link-blocking-first-paint.helpText: Link elements are blocking the first paint of your page. Consider inlining critical links and deferring non-critical ones. [Learn more](https://developers.google.com/web/tools/lighthouse/audits/blocking-resources).

no-document-write.name: no-document-write
no-document-write.helpText: For users on slow connections, external scripts dynamically injected via `document.write()` can delay page load by tens of seconds. [Learn more](https://developers.google.com/web/tools/lighthouse/audits/document-write).

no-mutation-events.name: no-mutation-events
no-mutation-events.description: Avoids Mutation Events in its own scripts
no-mutation-events.helpText: Mutation Events are deprecated and harm performance. Consider using Mutation Observers instead. [Learn more](https://developers.google.com/web/tools/lighthouse/audits/mutation-events).

no-websql.name: no-websql
no-websql.helpText: Web SQL is deprecated. Consider using IndexedDB instead. [Learn more](https://developers.google.com/web/tools/lighthouse/audits/web-sql).

notification-on-start.name: notification-on-start
notification-on-start.description: Avoids requesting the notification permission on page load
notification-on-start.helpText: Users are mistrustful of or confused by sites that request to send notifications without context. Consider tying the request to user gestures instead. [Learn more](https://developers.google.com/web/tools/lighthouse/audits/notifications-on-load).

password-inputs-can-be-pasted-into.name: password-inputs-can-be-pasted-into
password-inputs-can-be-pasted-into.description: Allows users to paste into password fields
password-inputs-can-be-pasted-into.helpText: Preventing password pasting undermines good security policy. [Learn more](https://www.ncsc.gov.uk/blog-post/let-them-paste-passwords)

header.text: Password inputs that prevent pasting into

script-blocking-first-paint.name: script-blocking-first-paint
script-blocking-first-paint.helpText: Script elements are blocking the first paint of your page. Consider inlining critical scripts and deferring non-critical ones. [Learn more](https://developers.google.com/web/tools/lighthouse/audits/blocking-resources).

uses-http2.displayValue: 10 requests were not handled over HTTP/2
uses-http2.name: uses-http2
uses-http2.description: Does not use HTTP/2 for all of its resources
uses-http2.helpText: HTTP/2 offers many benefits over HTTP/1.1, including binary headers, multiplexing, and server push. [Learn more](https://developers.google.com/web/tools/lighthouse/audits/http2).

uses-passive-event-listeners.name: uses-passive-event-listeners
uses-passive-event-listeners.description: Uses passive listeners to improve scrolling performance
uses-passive-event-listeners.helpText: Consider marking your touch and wheel event listeners as `passive` to improve your page's scroll performance. [Learn more](https://developers.google.com/web/tools/lighthouse/audits/passive-event-listeners).

reportCategories.name: Accessibility
reportCategories.description: These checks highlight opportunities to [improve the accessibility of your app](https://developers.google.com/web/fundamentals/accessibility).

result.name: accesskeys
result.helpText: Access keys let users quickly focus a part of the page. For proper navigation, each access key must be unique. [Learn more](https://dequeuniversity.com/rules/axe/2.2/accesskeys).

result.name: aria-allowed-attr
result.helpText: Each ARIA `role` supports a specific subset of `aria-*` attributes. Mismatching these invalidates the `aria-*` attributes. [Learn more](https://dequeuniversity.com/rules/axe/2.2/aria-allowed-attr).

result.name: aria-required-attr
result.helpText: Some ARIA roles have required attributes that describe the state of the element to screen readers. [Learn more](https://dequeuniversity.com/rules/axe/2.2/aria-required-attr).

result.name: aria-required-children
result.description: Elements with `[role]` that require specific children `[role]`s, are present.
result.helpText: Some ARIA parent roles must contain specific child roles to perform their intended accessibility functions. [Learn more](https://dequeuniversity.com/rules/axe/2.2/aria-required-children).

result.name: aria-required-parent
result.description: `[role]`s are contained by their required parent element.
result.helpText: Some ARIA child roles must be contained by specific parent roles to properly perform their intended accessibility functions. [Learn more](https://dequeuniversity.com/rules/axe/2.2/aria-required-parent).

result.name: aria-roles
result.helpText: ARIA roles must have valid values in order to perform their intended accessibility functions. [Learn more](https://dequeuniversity.com/rules/axe/2.2/aria-roles).

result.name: aria-valid-attr-value
result.helpText: Assistive technologies, like screen readers, can't interpret ARIA attributes with invalid values. [Learn more](https://dequeuniversity.com/rules/axe/2.2/aria-valid-attr-value).

result.name: aria-valid-attr
result.description: `[aria-*]` attributes are valid and not misspelled.
result.helpText: Assistive technologies, like screen readers, can't interpret ARIA attributes with invalid names. [Learn more](https://dequeuniversity.com/rules/axe/2.2/aria-valid-attr).

result.name: audio-caption
result.helpText: Captions make audio elements usable for deaf or hearing-impaired users, providing critical information such as who is talking, what they're saying, and other non-speech information. [Learn more](https://dequeuniversity.com/rules/axe/2.2/audio-caption).

result.name: button-name
result.helpText: When a button doesn't have an accessible name, screen readers announce it as "button", making it unusable for users who rely on screen readers. [Learn more](https://dequeuniversity.com/rules/axe/2.2/button-name).

result.name: bypass
result.description: The page contains a heading, skip link, or landmark region.
result.helpText: Adding ways to bypass repetitive content lets keyboard users navigate the page more efficiently. [Learn more](https://dequeuniversity.com/rules/axe/2.2/bypass).

result.name: color-contrast
result.description: Background and foreground colors do not have a sufficient contrast ratio.
result.helpText: Low-contrast text is difficult or impossible for many users to read. [Learn more](https://dequeuniversity.com/rules/axe/2.2/color-contrast).

result.name: definition-list
result.description: `<dl>`'s contain only properly-ordered `<dt>` and `<dd>` groups, `<script>` or `<template>` elements.
result.helpText: When definition lists are not properly marked up, screen readers may produce confusing or inaccurate output. [Learn more](https://dequeuniversity.com/rules/axe/2.2/definition-list).

result.name: dlitem
result.description: Definition list items are wrapped in `<dl>` elements.
result.helpText: Definition list items (`<dt>` and `<dd>`) must be wrapped in a parent `<dl>` element to ensure that screen readers can properly announce them. [Learn more](https://dequeuniversity.com/rules/axe/2.2/dlitem).

result.name: document-title
result.helpText: Screen reader users use page titles to get an overview of the contents of the page. [Learn more](https://dequeuniversity.com/rules/axe/2.2/document-title).

result.name: duplicate-id
result.description: `[id]` attributes on the page are unique.
result.helpText: The value of an id attribute must be unique to prevent other instances from being overlooked by assistive technologies. [Learn more](https://dequeuniversity.com/rules/axe/2.2/duplicate-id).

result.name: frame-title
result.helpText: Screen reader users rely on frame titles to describe the contents of frames. [Learn more](https://dequeuniversity.com/rules/axe/2.2/frame-title).

value.description: Ensures every HTML document has a lang attribute
value.help: <html> element must have a lang attribute

result.name: html-has-lang
result.description: `<html>` element does not have a `[lang]` attribute.
result.helpText: If a page doesn't specify a lang attribute, a screen reader assumes that the page is in the default language that the user chose when setting up the screen reader. If the page isn't actually in the default language, then the screen reader might not announce the page's text correctly. [Learn more](https://dequeuniversity.com/rules/axe/2.2/html-lang).

result.name: html-lang-valid
result.description: `<html>` element has a valid value for its `[lang]` attribute.
result.helpText: Specifying a valid [BCP 47 language](https://www.w3.org/International/questions/qa-choosing-language-tags#question) helps screen readers announce text properly. [Learn more](https://dequeuniversity.com/rules/axe/2.2/valid-lang).

result.name: image-alt
result.helpText: Informative elements should aim for short, descriptive alternate text. Decorative elements can be ignored with an empty alt attribute.[Learn more](https://dequeuniversity.com/rules/axe/2.2/image-alt).

result.name: input-image-alt
result.helpText: When an image is being used as an `<input>` button, providing alternative text can help screen reader users understand the purpose of the button. [Learn more](https://dequeuniversity.com/rules/axe/2.2/input-image-alt).

result.name: label
result.helpText: Labels ensure that form controls are announced properly by assistive technologies, like screen readers. [Learn more](https://dequeuniversity.com/rules/axe/2.2/label).

result.name: layout-table
result.description: Presentational `<table>` elements avoid using `<th>`, `<caption>` or the `[summary]` attribute.
result.helpText: A table being used for layout purposes should not include data elements, such as the th or caption elements or the summary attribute, because this can create a confusing experience for screen reader users. [Learn more](https://dequeuniversity.com/rules/axe/2.2/layout-table).

result.name: link-name
result.helpText: Link text (and alternate text for images, when used as links) that is discernible, unique, and focusable improves the navigation experience for screen reader users. [Learn more](https://dequeuniversity.com/rules/axe/2.2/link-name).

result.name: list
result.description: Lists contain only `<li>` elements and script supporting elements (`<script>` and `<template>`).
result.helpText: Screen readers have a specific way of announcing lists. Ensuring proper list structure aids screen reader output. [Learn more](https://dequeuniversity.com/rules/axe/2.2/list).

result.name: listitem
result.description: List items (`<li>`) are contained within `<ul>` or `<ol>` parent elements.
result.helpText: Screen readers require list items (`<li>`) to be contained within a parent `<ul>` or `<ol>` to be announced properly. [Learn more](https://dequeuniversity.com/rules/axe/2.2/listitem).

result.name: meta-refresh
result.description: The document does not use `<meta http-equiv="refresh">`.
result.helpText: Users do not expect a page to refresh automatically, and doing so will move focus back to the top of the page. This may create a frustrating or confusing experience. [Learn more](https://dequeuniversity.com/rules/axe/2.2/meta-refresh).

result.name: meta-viewport
result.description: `[user-scalable="no"]` is not used in the `<meta name="viewport">` element and the `[maximum-scale]` attribute is not less than 5.
result.helpText: Disabling zooming is problematic for users with low vision who rely on screen magnification to properly see the contents of a web page. [Learn more](https://dequeuniversity.com/rules/axe/2.2/meta-viewport).

result.name: object-alt
result.helpText: Screen readers cannot translate non-text content. Adding alt text to `<object>` elements helps screen readers convey meaning to users. [Learn more](https://dequeuniversity.com/rules/axe/2.2/object-alt).

result.name: tabindex
result.description: No element has a `[tabindex]` value greater than 0.
result.helpText: A value greater than 0 implies an explicit navigation ordering. Although technically valid, this often creates frustrating experiences for users who rely on assistive technologies. [Learn more](https://dequeuniversity.com/rules/axe/2.2/tabindex).

result.name: td-headers-attr
result.description: Cells in a `<table>` element that use the `[headers]` attribute only refer to other cells of that same table.
result.helpText: Screen readers have features to make navigating tables easier. Ensuring `<td>` cells using the `[headers]` attribute only refer to other cells in the same table may improve the experience for screen reader users. [Learn more](https://dequeuniversity.com/rules/axe/2.2/td-headers-attr).

result.name: th-has-data-cells
result.description: `<th>` elements and elements with `[role="columnheader"/"rowheader"]` have data cells they describe.
result.helpText: Screen readers have features to make navigating tables easier. Ensuring table headers always refer to some set of cells may improve the experience for screen reader users. [Learn more](https://dequeuniversity.com/rules/axe/2.2/th-has-data-cells).

result.name: valid-lang
result.helpText: Specifying a valid [BCP 47 language](https://www.w3.org/International/questions/qa-choosing-language-tags#question) on elements helps ensure that text is pronounced correctly by a screen reader. [Learn more](https://dequeuniversity.com/rules/axe/2.2/valid-lang).

result.name: video-caption
result.helpText: When a video provides a caption it is easier for deaf and hearing impaired users to access its information. [Learn more](https://dequeuniversity.com/rules/axe/2.2/video-caption).

result.name: video-description
result.helpText: Audio descriptions provide relevant information for videos that dialogue cannot, such as facial expressions and scenes. [Learn more](https://dequeuniversity.com/rules/axe/2.2/video-description).

reportCategories.name: Best Practices
reportCategories.description: We've compiled some recommendations for modernizing your web app and avoiding performance pitfalls. These audits do not affect your score but are worth a look.

result.name: appcache-manifest
result.helpText: Application Cache is deprecated. [Learn more](https://developers.google.com/web/tools/lighthouse/audits/appcache).

result.name: no-websql
result.helpText: Web SQL is deprecated. Consider using IndexedDB instead. [Learn more](https://developers.google.com/web/tools/lighthouse/audits/web-sql).

result.name: is-on-https
result.helpText: All sites should be protected with HTTPS, even ones that don't handle sensitive data. HTTPS prevents intruders from tampering with or passively listening in on the communications between your app and your users, and is a prerequisite for HTTP/2 and many new web platform APIs. [Learn more](https://developers.google.com/web/tools/lighthouse/audits/https).

result.displayValue: 10 requests were not handled over HTTP/2
result.name: uses-http2
result.description: Does not use HTTP/2 for all of its resources
result.helpText: HTTP/2 offers many benefits over HTTP/1.1, including binary headers, multiplexing, and server push. [Learn more](https://developers.google.com/web/tools/lighthouse/audits/http2).

result.name: uses-passive-event-listeners
result.description: Uses passive listeners to improve scrolling performance
result.helpText: Consider marking your touch and wheel event listeners as `passive` to improve your page's scroll performance. [Learn more](https://developers.google.com/web/tools/lighthouse/audits/passive-event-listeners).

result.name: no-mutation-events
result.description: Avoids Mutation Events in its own scripts
result.helpText: Mutation Events are deprecated and harm performance. Consider using Mutation Observers instead. [Learn more](https://developers.google.com/web/tools/lighthouse/audits/mutation-events).

result.name: no-document-write
result.helpText: For users on slow connections, external scripts dynamically injected via `document.write()` can delay page load by tens of seconds. [Learn more](https://developers.google.com/web/tools/lighthouse/audits/document-write).

result.name: external-anchors-use-rel-noopener
result.description: Does not open external anchors using `rel="noopener"`
result.helpText: Open new tabs using `rel="noopener"` to improve performance and prevent security vulnerabilities. [Learn more](https://developers.google.com/web/tools/lighthouse/audits/noopener).

result.name: geolocation-on-start
result.description: Avoids requesting the geolocation permission on page load
result.helpText: Users are mistrustful of or confused by sites that request their location without context. Consider tying the request to user gestures instead. [Learn more](https://developers.google.com/web/tools/lighthouse/audits/geolocation-on-load).

result.name: notification-on-start
result.description: Avoids requesting the notification permission on page load
result.helpText: Users are mistrustful of or confused by sites that request to send notifications without context. Consider tying the request to user gestures instead. [Learn more](https://developers.google.com/web/tools/lighthouse/audits/notifications-on-load).

result.name: deprecations
result.helpText: Deprecated APIs will eventually be removed from the browser. [Learn more](https://www.chromestatus.com/features#deprecated).

result.name: manifest-short-name-length
result.description: Manifest's `short_name` will be truncated when displayed on homescreen
result.helpText: Make your app's `short_name` fewer than 12 characters to ensure that it's not truncated on homescreens. [Learn more](https://developers.google.com/web/tools/lighthouse/audits/manifest-short_name-is-not-truncated).

result.name: password-inputs-can-be-pasted-into
result.description: Allows users to paste into password fields
result.helpText: Preventing password pasting undermines good security policy. [Learn more](https://www.ncsc.gov.uk/blog-post/let-them-paste-passwords)
